<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F, 2/4. Short two-beat bars. LH "33" triads, quarter notes for rhythmic drive.
- Gm/Bb alternate throughout as ii/IV. C7 dominant provides tension.
- A major (secondary dominant to Dm) substituted as ③/⑥m label.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH single-note line doubles melody at octave or third in quick passages.
- LH holds F2 common tone through F-Gm-F progressions.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light 2/4 bounce; builds to bar 12-13 (highest RH register); quiet F close.
-->
